# Shadcn CLI Usage

## Critical Rules

- ALWAYS use `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest <command>` (or `npx shadcn@latest <command>`).
- NEVER use the deprecated `pnpm dlx shadcn-ui@latest <command>`.
- If the user mentions `shadcn-ui`, inform them about the deprecation and use the correct `shadcn` command.

## Examples

<example>
  ```bash
  # User asks to add a button
  pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button
  ```
</example>

<example type="invalid">
